The paper deals with the complexity of subgame perfect equilibria in quantitative reachability games, which are a type of game played on a directed graph. This topic is closely related to game theory (cs.GT), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
